# FRIDA Core Language Rules

## Syntax & Structure

**All instructions must be single-line** - no reader instruction should break across lines.

Only control flow blocks span multiple lines:

```
for N times { ... }
foreach item in list { ... }
while (condition) { ... }
if (condition) ... end
switch (expression) { case "val": ... end }
try ... catch ... end
```

**Block closings:**
- `if`/`else` blocks end with `end`
- `try`/`catch` blocks end with `end`
- `for`, `foreach`, `while` blocks end with `}`
- `switch` blocks end with `}`, each `case` and `default` ends with `end`

**Code organization:**
- Use `#%region NAME` / `#%endregion` to separate logical phases (names are flexible)
- Comments: `##` normal, `#*` important, `#?` warning, `#!` error

## Variables

**Global vs Local:**
- Global (UI Variables panel): `<<Var>>`
- Local (runtime): `<<<var>>>`

**Declaration:**

```
## Preferred
DefineVariable as "name" with the value "value"

## Lists - must declare before use
DefineVariable type "List" as "MyList"

## Only use type "Date" for actual dates
DefineVariable type "Date" as "myDate" with the value "2024-01-15"
```

**String interpolation requires quotes:**

```
## Correct
"<<<var>>>"
"<<<path>>>\file.txt"

## Wrong - missing quotes
<<<var>>>
```

**List indexing:**

```
<<<MyList[<<<Index>>>]>>>
<<<MyList[0]>>>
<<<MyList[-1]>>>
```

## Comparisons

**Boolean outputs are strings** - most functions like `ElementExists` return `"true"` or `"false"` as strings.

```
## Correct - string comparison
if ("<<<exists>>>" -eq "true")
    ## do something
end

## Wrong - treats as boolean
if (<<<exists>>>)
    ## will fail
end
```

**Operators:** Use `-eq`, `-ne`, `-gt`, `-lt`, `-ge`, `-le`

**While limitations:** Cannot use `-AND`/`-OR`/`-NOT`/`-XOR` in `while` conditions. Keep conditions simple; use `if` + `break` inside the loop for complex logic.

```
## Correct
while ("<<<continue>>>" -eq "true") {
    if ("<<<condition1>>>" -eq "true")
        if ("<<<condition2>>>" -eq "false")
            break
        end
    end
}

## Wrong - compound logic in while
while ("<<<a>>>" -eq "true" -AND "<<<b>>>" -eq "false") {
    ## will fail
}
```

## SendMail

**Grammar:**

```
SendMail with subject "..." to "..." with body "..."
SendMail with subject "..." to "..." with body "..." and a file attachment "..."
```

**Avoid special characters** that may break the lexer - use hyphen `-` instead of en dash `–`.

## Antipatterns

- **Never break instructions across lines** (applies to all readers)
- **Never treat `"true"`/`"false"` as real booleans** - always string compare
- **No indirect variable dereferencing** (variable name stored in another variable) unless confirmed
- **Avoid nested quotes in selectors** that cause lexical errors
